The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Tuesday, August 24, 2004 				 Oslo hunt for Scream thieves
				 	 Edvard Munchs Scream																								Oslo, Aug. 23 (Reuters): Norways police sought to nail down the motive behind the theft of Edvard Munchs The Scream today amid criticism that Oslos museum security was too lax after gunmen stole the picture in a dramatic daylight raid.																								Police were following up tips telephoned in after yesterdays theft in front of dozens of terrified tourists at the Munch Museum. The scene of the crime, the getaway car and bits of wooden frame were all being scoured for clues.																								The robbers responsible for one of the art worlds most spectacular art thefts of recent years could plan to wrench a ransom from the Norwegian government, might have stolen to order for a reclusive collector or simply relish the picture as a trophy, criminologists said.																								We have many tips ... were keeping all possibilities open, Oslo assistant police chief Iver Stensrud said of the robbery of The Scream and Madonna, both Munch masterpieces and worth tens of millions of dollars. 
